================
named-admin 
================

Copyright (C) 2008 Nik Wolfgramm, licensed under GPL

named-admin.rb: command line tool for bind named.conf zone administration
Reads, writes and sorts the file and finds, inserts, deletes and counts zones

Usage:
	Search a zone by name:	 named-admin -s | --search-zone [zone name]
	Insert a zone by name:	 named-admin -i | --insert-zone [zone name]
	Delete a zone by name:	 named-admin -d | --delete-zone [zone name]
	Print (parsed, sorted):	 named-admin -p | --print
	Write (parsed, sorted):	 named-admin -w | --write
	Count number of zones:	 named-admin -c | --count--zones

Configuration:

config/config.yml
  - specify the default path to you named.conf bind configuration file
  - activate automatic syntax checking with named-checkconf

config/zones,yml
  - define different zone templates which can be used by the insert action